Note:
Unit tests for compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/aes_gcm.runa.

Test vectors:

KAT 1: AES-256-GCM both-empty case (McGrew & Viega "The Galois/Counter Mode
       of Operation (GCM)", May 2005, Test Case 13).
  Key:   00 (x32)
  IV:    00 (x12)
  PT:    (empty)
  AAD:   (empty)
  CT:    (empty)
  Tag:   53 0f 8a fb c7 45 36 b9 a9 63 b4 f1 c4 cb 73 8b

KAT 2: AES-256-GCM AAD-only with empty plaintext (NIST CAVP
       gcmEncryptExtIV256, Count 0 of [Keylen=256, IVlen=96, PTlen=0,
       AADlen=128, Taglen=128]).
  Key:   b5 2c 50 5a 37 d7 8e da 5d d3 4f 20 c2 25 40 ea
         1b 58 96 3c f8 e5 bf 8f fa 85 f9 f2 49 25 05 b4
  IV:    51 6c 33 92 9d f5 a3 28 4f f4 63 d7
  AAD:   3e 8b c5 ad e1 82 ff 6b 2e a9 b8 0e a7 f8 7c f3
  PT:    (empty)
  CT:    (empty)
  Tag:   ad a4 47 b3 e7 2c c7 2b 13 91 c4 f1 ee 2d a4 67

KAT 3: AES-256-GCM both AAD and plaintext non-empty (McGrew & Viega
       2005, Test Case 16).
  Key:   fe ff e9 92 86 65 73 1c 6d 6a 8f 94 67 30 83 08
         fe ff e9 92 86 65 73 1c 6d 6a 8f 94 67 30 83 08
  IV:    ca fe ba be fa ce db ad de ca f8 88
  PT:    d9 31 32 25 f8 84 06 e5 a5 59 09 c5 af f5 26 9a
         86 a7 a9 53 15 34 f7 da 2e 4c 30 3d 8a 31 8a 72
         1c 3c 0c 95 95 68 09 53 2f cf 0e 24 49 a6 b5 25
         b1 6a ed f5 aa 0d e6 57 ba 63 7b 39                (60 bytes)
  AAD:   fe ed fa ce de ad be ef fe ed fa ce de ad be ef
         ab ad da d2                                        (20 bytes)
  CT:    52 2d c1 f0 99 56 7d 07 f4 7f 37 a3 2a 84 42 7d
         64 3a 8c dc bf e5 c0 c9 75 98 a2 bd 25 55 d1 aa
         8c b0 8e 48 59 0d bb 3d a7 b0 8b 10 56 82 88 38
         c5 f6 1e 63 93 ba 7a 0a bc c9 f6 62                (60 bytes)
  Tag:   76 fc 6e ce 0f 4e 17 68 cd df 88 53 bb 2d 55 1b

Round-trip tests on KAT 3:
  - seal then open with valid tag yields the original plaintext.
  - open with mutated tag returns 0.
  - open with mutated ciphertext returns 0.
:End Note

Import "tests/test_utils.runa" as T
Import "runtime/core/memory/arena.runa" as Arena
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/aes_gcm.runa" as GCM

Process called "compare_bytes" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, length as Integer returns Integer:
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than length:
        Let ba be Memory.memory_get_byte(a, i)
        Let bb be Memory.memory_get_byte(b, i)
        If ba is not equal to bb:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "zero_buffer" takes buf as Integer, length as Integer returns Integer:
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than length:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, i, 0)
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: KAT 1: AES-256-GCM, all-zero key/IV, empty PT and empty AAD
Note: Expected tag: 53 0f 8a fb c7 45 36 b9 a9 63 b4 f1 c4 cb 73 8b
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "test_aes256_gcm_mcgrew_tc13_empty" that takes results as Integer returns Integer:
    T.begin_suite(results, "AES-256-GCM McGrew TC13 empty-empty")

    Let arena be Arena.arena_create(131072)
    T.assert_not_null(results, "arena created", arena)

    Let key be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 32)
    zero_buffer(key, 32)
    Let iv be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 12)
    zero_buffer(iv, 12)

    Let tag be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 16)
    zero_buffer(tag, 16)

    Let rc be GCM.aes_gcm_seal(arena, key, 32, iv, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, tag)
    T.assert_equal(results, "TC13 seal rc=1", rc, 1)

    Let expected_tag be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 16)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(expected_tag, 0, 83)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(expected_tag, 1, 15)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(expected_tag, 2, 138)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(expected_tag, 3, 251)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(expected_tag, 4, 199)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(expected_tag, 5, 69)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(expected_tag, 6, 54)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(expected_tag, 7, 185)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(expected_tag, 8, 169)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(expected_tag, 9, 99)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(expected_tag, 10, 180)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(expected_tag, 11, 241)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(expected_tag, 12, 196)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(expected_tag, 13, 203)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(expected_tag, 14, 115)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(expected_tag, 15, 139)

    Let tag_match be compare_bytes(tag, expected_tag, 16)
    T.assert_equal(results, "TC13 tag matches McGrew TC13", tag_match, 1)

    Note: Verify open with the correct tag succeeds
    Let open_rc be GCM.aes_gcm_open(arena, key, 32, iv, 0, 0, 0, 0, tag, 0)
    T.assert_equal(results, "TC13 open with valid tag returns 1", open_rc, 1)

    Arena.arena_destroy(arena)
    Return 1
End Process

